beer_brewer_name: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
review_blob: Maybe the Coppola of beer? Its a pleasant brew that, at cold temperatures, one can drink a lot of at a BBQ.

beer_brewer_name: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
review_blob: A nice bumpy head. Dark and woody taste with a very smooth and mellow finish.
A very nice pilsner. Aromatic, smooth, then a pleasing kind of pilsner finish.
A smooth and interesting beer. Not much of a nose or aroma - all the fun is on the back end.
beer_name: New Glarus Fat Squirrel Nut Brown Ale

review_blob: Smooth finish that turns a bit bitter at the end. Really enjoy the scent and the nose of the beer.
A pleasant brew. Smooth beginning and subtle honey sweetness lingers. Tastes good cold.

A bit of a dry finish. Perhaps I shouldnt have tried this for the first time whilst sick. Anyhow, my least favourite out of the Heater Allen beers Ive tried - but that says more about the quality of HA than this beer - which is not bad.
I tend to be more a dark beer person, but this surprised me. Flavorful, but smooth - without the bitter finish I find in a lot of pilsners.
Really interesting beer. Substantial taste, and it took a while to figure out the wine finish. The 9.5% made for a nice evening.
A beautiful dark colour. A smooth yet interesting taste. Dunkels are right near the top of my personal list.
Best beer of the Thursday tasting session. Great finish. Rich flavours throughout.
Whoa! Nice and dark. Smoky taste. Very palatable for a 9.5% beer. A top-five lifetime beer for Mac; not quite there for me, but very good.
Interesting blend of dark strength and hoppy pep, with the most extreme components of each kind of mellowed by the others presence. An interesting brew.
Maybe a bit fruity for me. I admire what they were trying to do, but perhaps it just wasnt the right night for it.
Smooth and smoky from start to finish. Looks great in the glass with a subtle aroma.
beer_name: Heater Allen Sandy Paws Baltic Porter (2010-)

review_blob: This is a beer of which I could consume indefinite quantities. Subtle but substantial hazlenut taste. Great finish.
Fantastic Oregon beer. Distinctive yet pleasing to many. Eminently drinkable.
Standard beer-hall beer. Kind of a pale color. Cheap European beer is so much beter than cheap American beer.
Beautiful golden beer in a 22 with a stylish label. Light, fresh, and hint of fruit. More bitter than I expected.
